main event: Four brightly glowing lights were observed moving at a high rate of speed for 5 minutes 70 miles SW of Walker AFB, N.M. on 15 Nov 54.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 5 minutes, providing a substantial duration for the witnesses to gather information.
The report mentions that there were photographs taken during the sighting, potentially providing visual evidence.
The conclusion indicates that it was initially thought to be a balloon, but the report remains inconclusive.
The location of the sighting, 70 miles SW of Walker AFB, N.M., is significant as it is an area strongly associated with military activity.
The report states that a field investigation was deemed impractical, raising questions about the thoroughness of the investigation process.
